Requires

   POSIX environment
   Standard POSIX /bin/sh
   Some web client: curl | wget | lynx

   Perl - only on system wide install with manual pages

SYSTEM WIDE

   make install

MINIMAL MANUAL INSTALL

   # Or:
   # 1. copy the binary whereever you want, like $HOME
   # 2. edit account's cron with "contab -e"

   install --mode=755 ddns-updater.sh /usr/local/bin/ddns-updater
   install --mode=644 cron.d/ddns-updater /etc/cron.d/

   mkdir --parents ~/.config/ddns-updater

INSTALL CONFIGURATION FILES

   Choos one of these directories:

      $HOME/.config/ddns-updater/	   or
      /etc/ddns-updater/

INSTALL CONFIGURATION TEMPLATES

   # Edit after copying and enable each one manually
   cp conf/*.conf $HOME/.config/ddns-updater/
